Dataset

This report includes the signatures for 30 files. A completed listing can be found at the end of the document.

Parameters

The following parameters have been used:

  • Unmixing Technique: Manually selected endmembers
  • Clustering Technique: Endmembers selected as centroids
  • No wavelength ranges have been cleaned at the beggining of the signature
  • No wavelength ranges have been cleaned at the end of the signature
  • No smoothing has been performed

Endmember classification

Endmember weights by cluster

The next two figures show the average mixture for each cluster among all endmembers. In the barplot Each column represents a single cluster and averages the weights of the contained signatures. The different colored segments of the bar represent the weight proportion for each endmember. The boxplot is analogous, with each box representing the distribution of weight for a particular endmember, separated in an individual plot for each cluster.
